// The synthetic implication ({...}) ==> r1 == r2 is unprovable from the
    // spec alone: the antecedent only ties r1 and r2 to the same set of
    // abstracted packets (un_acked_messages(src@)), which does not force a
    // canonical ordering on the underlying Vec<CPacket>. Two sequences with
    // the same `map_values(|p| p@).to_set()` can have different orderings,
    // so equality of the Vec<CPacket> values cannot be derived. Attempts
    // using extensional Seq equality (=~=) confirm this: Verus rejects the
    // step from set-equality to Seq-equality. We document this and emit no
    // unsound axioms; the determinism check legitimately flags the spec as
    // too weak.
